%% 3.1.5 Campus Management — sequence diagram (layered)
%% Actor > UI > Controller > Service > Repository > Database
%% BR05: Student create must set CampusId to an active campus — StudentService.ValidateCampusAsync

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Actor as Admin
    participant UI as UI (/campuses)
    participant CC as Controller (CampusController)
    participant CS as Service (CampusService)
    participant Repo as Repository (IRepository Campus)
    participant DB as Database (SQL Server)

    Actor->>UI: Open Campus Management (/campuses)
    UI->>CC: GET /api/Campus/Search
    CC->>CS: SearchCampusAsync(keyword, page, pageSize)
    CS->>Repo: Query campuses
    Repo->>DB: SELECT
    DB-->>Repo: rows
    Repo-->>CS: list
    CS-->>CC: PagedResult
    CC-->>UI: 200 — table (Code, Name, Address, Phone, ImageUrl, ...)

    Actor->>UI: Click Edit on first row
    UI->>UI: Form / Modal — edit fields including Contact Phone

    Actor->>UI: Replace phone with new Hotline, click Update

    UI->>CC: PUT /api/Campus/Update/{id} CampusUpdateDto
    CC->>CS: UpdateCampusAsync(id, dto)
    CS->>Repo: Update entity + SaveChangesAsync
    Repo->>DB: UPDATE Campus
    DB-->>Repo: OK
    Repo-->>CS: saved
    CS-->>CC: CampusDto
    CC-->>UI: 200 Success
    UI->>UI: Highlight row, refresh cell with new phone
    UI-->>Actor: Table shows latest number

    Note over Actor,DB: BR05 — Tạo tài khoản học sinh: bắt buộc CampusId trỏ tới campus đang active (POST Student/Create → StudentService.ValidateCampusAsync).
